# GitHub Packages Registry Configuration
# Copy this file to your project root as .npmrc
# Replace YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN with your Personal Access Token

# Configure GitHub Packages registry for @groxigo scope
@groxigo:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com

# Authentication token
# For local development, add this line with your Personal Access Token:
# //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN

# Or set as environment variable:
# export NPM_TOKEN=YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN

# To create a Personal Access Token:
# 1. Go to GitHub Settings > Developer settings > Personal access tokens > Tokens (classic)
# 2. Generate new token with 'read:packages' and 'write:packages' scopes
# 3. Use the token in your .npmrc file or as NPM_TOKEN environment variable

